{#-
  AlertDialog — destructive-confirm wrapper around Dialog.

  Per Ring 2 S2.2 doctrine [pending lock-in ADR]: AlertDialog is NOT a
  standalone compound — it's a wrapper that bakes Dialog's 3 destructive
  policies + injects a leading status icon:

    1. `closeOnEscape: false` — Esc does NOT dismiss.
    2. `closeOnBackdropClick: false` — backdrop click does NOT dismiss.
    3. `closeButton: false` — no close-X in header.
    4. Leading status icon in header (alert-triangle / alert-circle /
       info per `tone`).

  → The user MUST commit via an explicit Cancel or Confirm button. This
    matches WCAG SC 2.1.2 (no keyboard trap) because the footer's
    Cancel button is always keyboard-reachable via Tab.

  AlertDialog reuses the `dialog` Stimulus controller — no new controller.
  Events dispatched are `dialog:open` / `dialog:close` (consumer can wire
  these the same way as for plain Dialog).

  Per 12-microcopy-tone §Confirmations:
    - Title NAMES the resource ("Supprimer 'Arcelor' ?")
    - Body NAMES the consequence ("142 tâches perdues")
    - Confirm button NAMES the action ("Supprimer définitivement"),
      never generic "OK".
    - Cancel button comes FIRST in DOM order — flex-row writing
      direction handles LTR/RTL positioning naturally.

  Parameters:
    htmlId          (string, optional)  — auto-generated. Used to chain
                                          aria-labelledby + title's id.
    tone            (string, optional)  — danger (default) | warning | info.
                                          Drives the leading icon + the
                                          icon-wrap soft-color background.
    size            (string, optional)  — sm (default — confirms are short) |
                                          md | lg.
    open            (bool,   optional)  — false (default). SSR-open dialogs.
    className       (string, optional)  — extra classes on the outer wrap.
    dialogClassName (string, optional)  — extra classes on the `<dialog>`.

  Blocks:
    trigger (optional) — the element that opens the AlertDialog. Typically
                         a destructive Button. Consumer stamps
                         `data-action="click->dialog#open"`.
    title (required)   — the question / resource name. Wrapped in <h2>.
    body (required)    — the consequence statement. Optionally includes
                         a "type to confirm" Input.
    footer (required)  — button cluster. Standard pattern:
                         [Cancel secondary][Confirm <tone-aware>].
                         Consumer wires `data-action="click->dialog#close"`
                         on both (the Confirm typically runs its action
                         then closes, hence both close).
-#}

{%- set htmlId          = htmlId          | default('cremona-alert-dialog-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set tone            = tone            | default('danger') -%}
{%- set size            = size            | default('sm') -%}
{%- set open            = open            | default(false) -%}
{%- set className       = className       | default('') -%}
{%- set dialogClassName = dialogClassName | default('') -%}

{%- set _wrapClasses = ['cremona-dialog-wrap', 'cremona-alert-dialog-wrap'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _wrapClasses = _wrapClasses | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set _dialogClasses = ['cremona-dialog', 'cremona-alert-dialog'] -%}
{%- if dialogClassName -%}{%- set _dialogClasses = _dialogClasses | merge([dialogClassName]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set _titleId = htmlId ~ '-title' -%}

{%- set _iconName = {
  'danger':  'alert-triangle',
  'warning': 'alert-circle',
  'info':    'info'
}[tone] | default('alert-triangle') -%}

{%- set alertDialogHtmlId = htmlId -%}
{%- set alertDialogTitleId = _titleId -%}

<div
  class="{{ _wrapClasses | join(' ') }}"
  data-controller="dialog"
  data-dialog-open-value="{{ open ? 'true' : 'false' }}"
  data-dialog-close-on-escape-value="false"
  data-dialog-close-on-backdrop-click-value="false"
>
  {%- if block('trigger') is defined and block('trigger') is not empty -%}
    {%- block trigger -%}{%- endblock -%}
  {%- endif -%}

  <dialog
    id="{{ htmlId }}"
    class="{{ _dialogClasses | join(' ') }}"
    data-dialog-target="dialog"
    data-size="{{ size }}"
    data-tone="{{ tone }}"
    aria-labelledby="{{ _titleId }}"
  >
    <header class="cremona-dialog__header cremona-alert-dialog__header">
      <span class="cremona-alert-dialog__icon-wrap" aria-hidden="true">
        {% include '@cremona/components/icon/icon.html.twig' with { name: _iconName, size: 'md', decorative: true } %}
      </span>
      <h2 id="{{ _titleId }}" class="cremona-dialog__title cremona-alert-dialog__title">
        {%- block title -%}{%- endblock -%}
      </h2>
    </header>

    <div class="cremona-dialog__body cremona-alert-dialog__body">
      {%- block body -%}{%- endblock -%}
    </div>

    <footer class="cremona-dialog__footer cremona-alert-dialog__footer">
      {%- block footer -%}{%- endblock -%}
    </footer>
  </dialog>
</div>
